https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-subarray/description/

Question:
Input: nums = [-2,1,-3,4,-1,2,1,-5,4]
Output: 6
Explanation: The subarray [4,-1,2,1] has the largest sum 6.

SOLUTION:
You can do NAIVE approach with O(n2) but the optimal approach is using the localsum global sum which is described
[-2,1,-3,4,-1,2,1,-5,4]
Local sum checked addition of continuous elements is better or localsum vs globalsum is better

 localSum         GlobalSum
    -2                -2
max(-2+1,1)1       (-2,1)1
max(1-3,-3)-2      (-2,1)1
max(-2+4,4)4        (1,4)4
max(4-1,-1)3        (3,4)4 -> [4,-1]
max(3+2,2)5        (5,4)5  -> [4,-1,2]
max(5+1,1)6        (6,5)6  -> [4,-1,2,1]
max(6-5,-5)1        (6,1)6
max(1+4,5)5          (6,5)6

[4,-1,2,1]

class Solution {
    public int maxSubArray(int[] nums) {
        int localsum=nums[0],globalsum=nums[0];
        for(int i=1;i<nums.length;i++){
            localsum=Math.max(localsum+nums[i],nums[i]);
            globalsum=Math.max(localsum,globalsum);
        }
        return globalsum;
    }
}
